      • retrieveMessage

        public java.lang.String retrieveMessage()
        Pops off the first packet in the input buffer. Returns null if the buffer is empty.

        Intended to be used in a loop by a formal, global handler.

        Returns:
        the first packet in the input buffer, or null if the buffer is empty.
